# FFmpeg Workaround Handbook

Website:
https://ffmpeg.org/

## Steps to develop the application

1. Install Required Dependencies

pip install kivy
pip install pyinstaller

2. Download and install FFmpeg for Windows

a. Go to the official FFmpeg website: https://ffmpeg.org/download.html.

b. Under the "Get packages & executable files" section, find Windows.

c. Click the link under "Windows builds from gyan.dev" (this is a reliable third-party source).

d. On the new page, scroll down to the release builds section and download the latest version under the      “Essential Builds” category (e.g., ffmpeg-release-essentials.zip).

3. Create the Application UI with Kivy

Note:
To Rotate video file in the Windows media player
Ctl + Shift + R